{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c79e1593-a3c4-4c7f-972f-4202c8008f7e","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"0.5.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Add the MTP property** to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly (MTP makes it an executable):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio` — they should **not** coexist.\n- Keep your `xunit` (or `xunit.core`) 2.9.3 package as-is.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` routes through MTP instead of VSTest.\n- MTP turns your test project into a standalone executable with its own CLI (`--help` to explore).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"499c7ecf-ed89-4a3b-a6e3-7ec1d59b1eda","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"BD12:28D4C6:1C4CDAB:1FF6A73:6A07C429"},"id":"bd618a04-3ccd-4673-9790-8b0b280bc400","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:11:15.083Z","parentId":"5ae758fd-289d-4eb8-859e-5c464e11518c"}
